Text.Value: Return to the docks, or the deaths of everyone inside will be on your conscience.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
[Gortash videocalls]

A Scry Screen within the submersible flickers into life. Gortash, secure in his office, appears. He's angry.|

Text.Value: Intruders! Lord Gortash's orders were clear, the Iron Throne must be destroyed!
*Your conscience pricks - you did agree to an alliance, after all. But then again, what honour need there be with someone like Gortash?*
*And what of Duke Ravengard? Wyll may never forgive you if you abandon his father to this fate.*

EditorData.logicalname: WYLL COM ON MISSION TO SAVE FATHER

Text.Value: Hah! Are you now? Set foot within the Iron Throne and you will die. As will all of the hostages inside.
And I thought we were friends.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Performed to scrying screen - like a video cal
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Only plays if players made a deal with Gortash.

Text.Value: And your intelligence. Your presence here is a threat to the survival of the hostages inside the Iron Throne.
Aren't you the intrepid little adventurer. Digging and diving where you don't belong.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Performed to scrying screen - like a video call

Text.Value: Let the hostages go.
Return to the city, find Orin, and claim her Netherstone as you agreed to do. And then I will forget this transgression.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: only if on the quest to kill Orin

Text.Value: *How many people are trapped within? How many lives will be lost?*
Whatever you're hiding down here, I'm going to take it.
Tsk. You've been spending too much time with young Karlach - it's affecting your manners.
Cut the crap, Gortash. I go where I choose, and I'm curious about what's down here.
Whyever would I do that? The Iron Throne is their home.
What the hells is this place?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
[SHOWING THE DAMAGE]

The submersible drives onward toward the collapsing Iron Throne, maneuvering its way through the debris. 

The spotlight hits one of the upper levels in which civilian gnomes and humans can be seen inside a glass-walled holding cell, which is already damaged. The submarine pans downard, passing another cell in which Grand Duke Ranvegard can be seen (provided Gortash's coronation already happened). He is calm, despite the chaos, thanks to his tadpole.
EditorData.SFXTags: [TK] Accelerating engine. Large sounds of collapsing metal + pressure implosions.
EditorData.VFXTags: [TK] Bubbles as the submersible descends. Dust kicked up as submersible scrapes the floor.

Text.Value: Fuck you, Gortash.
It is a most useful tool for motivating my Gondian workforce - key to the construction of the Steel Watch that keep the city safe.
That was a mistake. When the corpses start to wash up on the shore, remember - you could have prevented all of this.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
[SUBMERSIBLE FINDS IRON THRONE]

The party travels with the submersible to the underwater Iron Throne building. A lightbeam spotlights the water in front of the submersible, seeing nothing but murky water until the Iron Throne comes into view - a ruined, submerged multi-storey building, topped by new, domed construction.

Text.Value: Dock at the Iron Throne.
*Not to mention your father. Captured, enthralled. He will surely perish if you do not intervene. His last breath taken as a slave to the Absolute.*

EditorData.logicalname: AVATAR WYLL ON MISSION TO SAVE FATHER

Text.Value: Wise. I'll see you soon.
But like all tools, the moment it ceases to be useful, I will break it. Thanks to your trespassing, that moment may have come.
Turn the submersible around and retreat.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
[Sub retreats]

The screen goes dark as Gortash salutes sarcastically, and the submersible turns around and heads back to the docks.

EditorData.stateContext: Performed to scrying screen - like a video call

Text.Value: I warned you to stay away once. I don't do second warnings.
What are you doing here?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
[DOCKING]

The submarine continues to pan downward through debris-strewn waters, reaching a bay on the topmost level, where it docks with a thunk.

Text.Value: Wrong. Your presence here is the only real threat to their survival.
I have prepared for this eventuality, and if you interfere, I will destroy the Iron Throne.
Might be facing Gortash sooner than we thought.

EditorData.NodeContext: Low and angry, expecting him to appear somewhere but she's not sure where.

Text.Value: I'm here to rescue the hostages, Gortash.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: has mission from Steel Watch Foundry

Text.Value: The Iron Throne. A ruin from the city's dark past that could become a template for a brighter future.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
[SUBMERSIBLE POWERS DOWN,]

As the party look on the building in wonder, the submersible engines power down and it comes to a stop. The spotlight flickers and then dies, leaving the submersible in darkness. Then the power returns, engines hum, and the spotlight kicks back into life.
EditorData.VFXTags: [TK] Searchlight beams from the submersible scanning the water [SG]

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: In respone to Gortash pressing the button, a series of explosion errupt around the submerged Iron Throne.
EditorData.SFXTags: [TK] Eyebeams underwater, crumpling metal, pipes with water-spray

Text.Value: Dead, they are no use to me. So I keep them safe, after a fashion.
*Your mind turns to the Gondian hostages, bound in fear, their futures hanging by a thread in Gortash's web.*

Synopsis: Players use the submersible to travel to the Iron Throne submersed building. On the way, spectator guards meet them and trigger the explosives on the upper dome of the facility. With little time before the prison facilities collapse, the players dock with the station, aiming to save the prisoners before it's destroyed.
